This workflow aims to find the correlation between average Satisfaction of life within different
countries and some variables chosen by the research team, namely greenhouse emission,
life expectancy, weekly working hours, employment rate, population and GDP per capita.
For this we imported data of the explanatory variables for each European country from
Eurostat using SQL. Dowloaded average satisfaction using API from Eurostat. Got population
and GDP data from the World Bank with R scrips and downladed a table with the country
codes to use it as a linktable.
Please enter your own path if you
want to write out the charts to files
